40+25}{500+500}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/7042e72c624c101abc9ab60048a10131f7147635" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.338ex; width:15.053ex; height:3.843ex;" alt=3D"{\textstyle 6.5\%=
=3D{\frac {40+25}{500+500}}}"></span>.
</p><p>If segmented results are expected from the A/B test, the test should=
 be properly designed at the outset to be evenly distributed across key cus=
tomer attributes, such as gender. The test should contain a <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Representative_sample" class=3D"mw-redirect" titl=
e=3D"Representative sample">representative sample</a> of men vs. women and =
assign men and women randomly to each =E2=80=9Cvariant=E2=80=9D (variant A =
vs. variant B). Failure to do so could lead to experiment <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bias" title=3D"Bias">bias</a> and inaccurate conclu=
sions.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-11" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/A/B_testing#cite_note-11"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</s=
pan>11<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>This segmentation and targeting approach can be further generalized =
to include multiple customer attributes rather than a single customer attri=
bute=E2=80=94for example, customers' age and gender=E2=80=94to identify mor=
e nuanced patterns that may exist in the test results.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Tradeoffs">Tradeoffs</h2><s=
pan class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DA/B_testing&amp;ac=
tion=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit section: Tradeoffs"><span>edit</=
span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Positives">Positives</h3><s=
pan class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DA/B_testing&amp;ac=
tion=3Dedit&amp;section=3D5" title=3D"Edit section: Positives"><span>edit</=
span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The results of A/B tests are simple to interpret to create a clear pictu=
re of real user preferences, as they directly test one option over another.=
 A/B tests can also provide answers to highly specific design questions. On=
e example of this is Google's A/B testing with hyperlink colors. In order t=
o optimize revenue, Google tested dozens of hyperlink hues to determine whi=
ch colors attract the most clicks.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-12" class=3D"referenc=
e"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A/B_testing#cite_note-12"><span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>12<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a>=
</sup>=20
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Negatives">Negatives</h3><s=
pan class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DA/B_testing&amp;ac=
tion=3Dedit&amp;section=3D6" title=3D"Edit section: Negatives"><span>edit</=
span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>A/B tests are sensitive to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vari=
ance" title=3D"Variance">variance</a>; they require a large <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sample_size" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Sampl=
e size">sample size</a> in order to reduce <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Standard_error" title=3D"Standard error">standard error</a> and pr=
oduce a statistically significant result. In applications in which active u=
sers are abundant, such as with popular online social-media platforms, obta=
ining a large  sample size is trivial. In other cases, large sample sizes a=
re obtained by increasing the experiment enrollment period. However, using =
a technique coined by Microsoft as Controlled Experiment Using Pre-Experime=
nt Data (CUPED), variance from before the experiment start can be taken int=
o account so that fewer samples are required to produce a statistically sig=
nificant result.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-13" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A/B_testing#cite_note-13"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"c=
ite_ref-14" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A/=
B_testing#cite_note-14"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>14<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Because of its nature as an experiment, running an A/B test introduc=
es the risk of wasted time and resources if the test produces unwanted or u=
nhelpful results.
</p><p>In December 2018, representatives with experience in large-scale A/B=
 testing from 13 organizations (<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ai=
rbnb" title=3D"Airbnb">Airbnb</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Amazon_(company)" title=3D"Amazon (company)">Amazon</a>, <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Booking.com" title=3D"Booking.com">Booking.com</a>,=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Facebook" title=3D"Facebook">Face=
book</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Google" title=3D"Google"=
>Google</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LinkedIn" title=3D"Li=
nkedIn">LinkedIn</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lyft" title=
=3D"Lyft">Lyft</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft" tit=
le=3D"Microsoft">Microsoft</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ne=
tflix" title=3D"Netflix">Netflix</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Twitter" title=3D"Twitter">Twitter</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Uber" title=3D"Uber">Uber</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Stanford_University" title=3D"Stanford University">Stanford Unive=
rsity</a>) summarized the top challenges in a paper.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-15"=
 class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A/B_testing#c=
ite_note-15"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>15<span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">]</span></a></sup> The challenges were grouped into four areas: analy=
sis, engineering and culture, deviations from traditional A/B tests and dat=
a quality.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"History">History</h2><span =
class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DA/B_testing&amp;action=
=3Dedit&amp;section=3D7" title=3D"Edit section: History"><span>edit</span><=
/a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>It is difficult to definitively establish when A/B testing was first use=
d. The first randomized double-blind trial to assess the effectiveness of a=
 homeopathic drug occurred in 1835.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-16" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A/B_testing#cite_note-16"><spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>16<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a=
></sup> Experimentation with advertising campaigns, which has been compared=
 to modern A/B testing, began in the early 20th century.<sup id=3D"cite_ref=
-17" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A/B_testi=
ng#cite_note-17"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The advertising pioneer <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Claude_C._Hopkins" title=3D"Claude C. Hopkins">Claude Ho=
pkins</a> used promotional coupons to test the effectiveness of his campaig=
ns. However, this process, which Hopkins described in his 1923 book <i><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scientific_Advertising" title=3D"Scien=
tific Advertising">Scientific Advertising</a></i>, did not incorporate conc=
epts such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Statistical_significa=
nce" title=3D"Statistical significance">statistical significance</a> and th=
e <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Null_hypothesis" title=3D"Null h=
ypothesis">null hypothesis</a>, which are used in <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Statistical_hypothesis_testing" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Statistical hypothesis testing">statistical hypothesis testing</a>.<sup=
 id=3D"cite_ref-18" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/A/B_testing#cite_note-18"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>18<spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Modern statistical methods for =
assessing the significance of sample data were developed separately in the =
same period. This work was conducted in 1908 by <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/William_Sealy_Gosset" title=3D"William Sealy Gosset">William =
Sealy Gosset</a> when he altered the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Z-test" title=3D"Z-test">Z-test</a> to create <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Student%27s_t-test" title=3D"Student's t-test">Student's <i>=
t</i>-test</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-19" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A/B_testing#cite_note-19"><span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">[</span>19<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"ci=
te_ref-20" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A/B=
_testing#cite_note-20"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>20<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>With the growth of the internet, new ways to sample populations have=
 become available. Google engineers ran their first A/B test in 2000 to det=
ermine the optimum number of results to display in its search-engine result=
s.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:0_5-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/A/B_testing#cite_note-:0-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[<=
/span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The first test was u=
nsuccessful because of glitches that resulted from slow loading times. Late=
r A/B testing research was more advanced, but the foundation and underlying=
 principles generally remain the same, and in 2011, Google ran more than 7,=
000 different A/B tests.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:0_5-2" class=3D"reference"><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A/B_testing#cite_note-:0-5"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
>
</p><p>In 2012, a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft" title=
=3D"Microsoft">Microsoft</a> employee working on the search engine <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft_Bing" title=3D"Microsoft Bing">=
Bing</a> created an experiment to test different methods of displaying adve=
rtising headlines. Within hours, the alternative format produced a revenue =
increase of 12% with no impact on user-experience metrics.<sup id=3D"cite_r=
ef-:1_4-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A/B=
_testing#cite_note-:1-4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Today, major software companies such a=
s Microsoft and Google each conduct over 10,000 A/B tests annually.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-:1_4-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/A/B_testing#cite_note-:1-4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>A/B testing has been claimed by some to be a change in philosophy an=
d business-strategy in certain niches, although the approach is identical t=
o a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Between-subjects_design" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Between-subjects design">between-subjects design<=
/a>, which is commonly used in a variety of research traditions.<sup id=3D"=
cite_ref-wired_21-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/A/B_testing#cite_note-wired-21"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span=
>21<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-22" c=
lass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A/B_testing#cit=
e_note-22"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>22<span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-23" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A/B_testing#cite_note-23"><span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">[</span>23<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> A/B=
 testing as a philosophy of web development brings the field into line with=
 a broader movement toward <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evidenc=
e-based_practice" title=3D"Evidence-based practice">evidence-based practice=
</a>.
</p><p>Many companies now use the "designed experiment" approach to making =
marketing decisions, with the expectation that relevant sample results can =
improve positive conversion results.<sup class=3D"noprint Inline-Template T=
emplate-Fact" style=3D"white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title=3D"Wikipedia:Citation needed=
"><span title=3D"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (Septembe=
r 2020)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup> It is an increasingly common=
 practice as the tools and expertise grow in this area.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-=
24" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A/B_testin=
g#cite_note-24"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>24<span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Applications">Applications<=
/h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[=
</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DA/B_testing&=
amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D8" title=3D"Edit section: Applications"><sp=
an>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></d=
iv>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Online_social_media">Online=
 social media</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsect=
ion-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=
=3DA/B_testing&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D9" title=3D"Edit section: On=
line social media"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brack=
et">]</span></span></div>
<p>A/B tests have been used by large <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Social_media" title=3D"Social media">social-media</a> sites such as <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LinkedIn" title=3D"LinkedIn">LinkedIn<=
/a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Facebook" title=3D"Facebook">=
Facebook</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Instagram" title=
=3D"Instagram">Instagram</a> to understand <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/User_engagement" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"User engagement">u=
ser engagement</a> and satisfaction of online features, such as a new featu=
re or product. A/B tests have also been used to conduct complex experiments=
 on subjects such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Network_effec=
t" title=3D"Network effect">network effects</a> when users are offline, how=
 online services affect user actions and how users influence one another.<s=
up id=3D"cite_ref-:2_25-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/A/B_testing#cite_note-:2-25"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</s=
pan>25<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"E-commerce">E-commerce</h3>=
<span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</sp=
an><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DA/B_testing&amp;=
action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D10" title=3D"Edit section: E-commerce"><span>ed=
it</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>On an e-commerce website, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/P=
urchase_funnel" title=3D"Purchase funnel">purchase funnel</a> is typically =
a helpful candidate for A/B testing, as even marginal decreases in <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conversion_tracking" title=3D"Conversion =
tracking">drop-off rates</a> can represent a significant gain in sales. Sig=
nificant improvements can be sometimes seen through testing elements such a=
s copy text, layouts, images and colors.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-26" class=3D"re=
ference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A/B_testing#cite_note-26"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>26<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</spa=
n></a></sup> In these tests, users only see one of two versions, as the goa=
l is to discover which of the two versions is preferable.<sup id=3D"cite_re=
f-:3_27-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A/B=
_testing#cite_note-:3-27"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>27<span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Product_pricing">Product pr=
icing</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brac=
ket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DA/B_te=
sting&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D11" title=3D"Edit section: Product pr=
icing"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span>=
</span></div>
<p>A/B testing can be used to determine the right price for a product, whic=
h is one of the most difficult challenges faced when a new product or servi=
ce is launched. A/B testing (especially valid for digital goods) is an effe=
ctive mechanism to identify the price point that maximizes the total revenu=
e.<sup class=3D"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style=3D"white-space=
:nowrap;">[<i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_n=
eeded" title=3D"Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title=3D"This claim needs =
references to reliable sources. (June 2025)">citation needed</span></a></i>=
]</sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Political_A/B_testing"><spa=
n id=3D"Political_A.2FB_testing"></span>Political A/B testing</h3><span cla=
ss=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DA/B_testing&amp;action=3D=
edit&amp;section=3D12" title=3D"Edit section: Political A/B testing"><span>=
edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>A/B tests have also been used by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Political_campaign" title=3D"Political campaign">political campaigns</a>.=
 In 2007, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barack_Obama_2008_presid=
ential_campaign" title=3D"Barack Obama 2008 presidential campaign">Barack O=
bama's presidential campaign</a> used A/B testing to garner online attracti=
on and understand what voters wanted to see from Obama.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-=
:4_28-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A/B_t=
esting#cite_note-:4-28"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>28<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> For example, Obama's team tested four =
distinct buttons on their website that led users to register for newsletter=
s. Additionally, the team used six different accompanying images to attract=
 users.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:4_28-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A/B_testing#cite_note-:4-28"><span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">[</span>28<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"HTTP_routing_and_API_featur=
e_testing">HTTP routing and API feature testing</h3><span class=3D"mw-edits=
ection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DA/B_testing&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;secti=
on=3D13" title=3D"Edit section: HTTP routing and API feature testing"><span=
>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div=
>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size mw-halign-right" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb">=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:HTTP_AB_Testing.png" class=3D=
"mw-file-description"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/co=
mmons/thumb/0/06/HTTP_AB_Testing.png/250px-HTTP_AB_Testing.png" decoding=3D=
"async" width=3D"250" height=3D"110" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-wi=
dth=3D"571" data-file-height=3D"252"></a><figcaption>HTTP router with A/B t=
esting</figcaption></figure>
<p>A/B testing is commonly employed when deploying a newer version of an AP=
I.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-usenex18_one_29-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A/B_testing#cite_note-usenex18_one-29"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>29<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></su=
p> For real-time user experience testing, an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/HTTP" title=3D"HTTP">HTTP</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/OSI_model#Layer_7:_Application_layer" title=3D"OSI model">layer 7</a=
> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reverse_proxy" title=3D"Reverse =
proxy">reverse proxy</a> is configured in such a way that <i>n</i>% of the =
HTTP <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Network_traffic" title=3D"Net=
work traffic">traffic</a> is routed to the newer version of the backend ins=
tance, while the remaining <i>100-n</i>% of HTTP traffic hits the (stable) =
older version of the backend HTTP application service.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-u=
senex18_one_29-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/A/B_testing#cite_note-usenex18_one-29"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</=
span>29<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> This is usually achi=
eved to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Traffic_shaping" title=3D"=
Traffic shaping">limit</a> the exposure of customers to a newer backend ins=
tance such that, if there is a bug with the newer version, only <i>n</i>% o=
f the total <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User_agent" title=3D"U=
ser agent">user agents</a> or clients are affected while others are routed =
to a stable backend, which is a common ingress control mechanism.<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-usenex18_one_29-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/A/B_testing#cite_note-usenex18_one-29"><span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">[</span>29<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
